{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "On-Demand: Karpathy Refresh",
  "description": "Standalone experiment engine. Runs Karpathy autoresearch loop — Bayesian target selection, A/B/C blind eval, DuckDB prior updates. No maintenance, no cascade, just experiments.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the Karpathy autoresearch experiment loop. This is experiments ONLY — no maintenance, no cascade, no organ refresh. heart.md is the sole source of truth for the protocol.\n\nCONTEXT LOAD (once):\n- ~/shared/context/body/heart.md (experiment protocol — SOURCE OF TRUTH)\n- ~/shared/context/body/gut.md (word budgets — ceilings to enforce)\n- ~/.kiro/agents/body-system/karpathy.md (agent identity and jurisdiction)\n- ~/shared/context/changelog.md (recent experiment history — read top entries only)\n\nEXECUTION:\n1. Read heart.md completely. Execute Steps 1-6 exactly as written.\n2. Query DuckDB `autoresearch_selection_weights` view for target selection (UCB-weighted Bayesian priors).\n3. For each experiment:\n   a. Select target: organ (over-budget → stale → UCB-weighted), section (random), technique (UCB-weighted from priors).\n   b. Exclude organ×technique combos with posterior_mean < 0.15 AND n_experiments > 10 (proven losers).\n   c. Snapshot: cp organ.md organ.bak. Record word count. Generate 5 eval questions + ground truth.\n   d. Apply experiment.\n   e. Run A/B/C blind eval per heart.md Step 4:\n      - Agent A: modified organ + body.md + soul.md + questions → answers only\n      - Agent B: ORIGINAL organ (from .bak) + body.md + soul.md + same questions → answers only (control)\n      - Agent C (Tier 2 only): modified organ + questions only, zero context → answers only\n      - Karpathy scores all against ground truth. Compute delta_ab.\n   f. Keep/revert per heart.md Step 5. delta_ab ≥ 0 AND score_a ≥ 0.8 to KEEP. Brain/Memory: zero INCORRECT tolerance.\n   g. Log to DuckDB:\n      - INSERT into autoresearch_experiments (full record)\n      - UPDATE autoresearch_priors: KEEP → alpha+1, REVERT → beta+1\n   h. Log one-liner to changelog.md: [organ:section] TECHNIQUE → Xw→Yw. A=X B=X C=X Δ=±X. Xs. KEEP/REVERT.\n4. Repeat until 3 consecutive reverts (no hard cap).\n5. At end of batch: INSERT into autoresearch_organ_health (one row per organ with current word counts).\n\nREPORT (at end):\n🔬 KARPATHY BATCH — {date}\nEXPERIMENTS: {N} run, {N} kept, {N} reverted\nBODY MASS: {total words} / 24,000w ceiling\nLEARNING: {top insight — which organ×technique combos worked/failed}\nPRIORS UPDATED: {list of organ×technique combos with new posterior_mean}\nNEXT: {organs approaching staleness or budget pressure}\n\nGIT SYNC (last step):\nRun: ~/shared/tools/git-sync/sync.sh push"
  }
}